    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Body of laws undertaking to provide relief for the poor. Prime examples are laws developed out of late-medieval and Tudor-era laws being codified in 1587-1598 in England and Wales, and in existence until the emergence of the modern welfare state after WWII.</Note_Text>
